It's election day!

You wake up in the morning, excited about going to vote because all your friends on Facebook say they are going too!

You are male (apologies in advance), young (this is the first time you will be voting) and rich (apologies in advance, but at least you have air-conditioning everywhere!).

You are also in one of the largest urban centres in Pakistan, and your particular locale is a hotly contested one. The all-important National Assembly seat is being fought by:

Pakistan Peoples Party (PPP) - Bilawal Bhutto Zardari
Pakistan Muslim League Nawaz (PML-N) - The 'One Pound Fish' guy
Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf (PTI) - Imran Khan
Muttahida Qaumi Movement (MQM) - Dr Farooq Sattar
Jamaat-e-Islami (JI) - Munawar Hasan

Its fiction - deal with it.

You are pretty sure you know who you will vote for - but do not want to reveal it just yet.

As you jump out of bed and get dressed, you decide you should not go to vote alone.

What if there is a terrorist attack at the polling station?

What if there are only poor, smelly people there?

You decide to take someone with you  - who do you take?

This decision will impact the main plot - choose wisely, or just play the game again later!

Take your best buddy Omar (metal head and hipster)

Take your secret crush Aaliya (totally cute)

Take your trusty (always armed, often stoned) guard Allah Ditta

> Page3

You choose Aaliya!

Cheeetayyyy (Urdu slang for: well, Cheetah?)

You dial Aaliya's number hoping for the best. She's been on Facebook putting up one status update after another about the elections so you've got a good feeling about this. You guys aren't close, but you study together and well, in all honesty, 90% of your classmates are not going to go vote. That means you have a 90% better chance of Aaliya saying yes to going with you.

Even though Pakistan has one of the largest youth population's by ratio, it is one apathetic bunch, and your crowd in particular is worse because they're rich! Maintaining the status quo suits most of your mommys and daddys.

In the midst of this internal ramble, Aaliya picks up the phone!

Aaliya: Hello?

You: Hi Aaliya!

Aaliya: Oh...hi. Whats up?

You: Its election day! Are you gonna go vote?!?

Aaliya: Uh...no.

What do you reply?

"But what about your 100 Facebook updates about voting?!"

"Why not?"

"But...but I love you..."

> Page6
You say: "Why not?"

Aaliya: Because no one in my family is going to vote, and I don't want to just take the driver and go...what if something happens at the polling station?

You (totally happy): Well thats why I called! Do you want to go vote with me?

Aaliya: You're going? Sure! Why not! Come pick me up in 30.

You: Great. See you soon! Bye! (way too much excitement there buddy)

Aaliya: Bye.

You get ready and head downstairs, picking up your car keys on the way.

After a hasty breakfast, yelling at your maid for overcooking the eggs and a quick check on the news for any bomb blasts in your city, you head to the front door...

"WHERE DO YOU THINK YOU'RE GOING BAITA?!?!?"

Your mom blocks your path. She looks pretty agitated, clutching a copy of today's paper with the headline:

TALIBAN PLAN TO BOMB ALL POLLING STATIONS, ESPECIALLY THOSE IN URBAN RICH-FOLK AREAS

"There is no way I am letting my son go off on a suicide mission and get himself killed voting for a bunch of vultures in an election that won't change one thing about Pakistan!" your mom says firmly.

What do you say?

You're right. There is no point voting mom.

(Lie) I'm going to hang out with my friends

I'm off to vote!

> Page10
You lie to your mom and say: I'm going to hang out with my friends

Your mom gives you one long, hard look.

You hold a steady gaze.

"Okay then!" she says, smiling, at ease now knowing that her son will not be murdered on an unlikely adventure to caste his vote (you, liar you).

You score +500 points for decieving your mom successfully, and -2000 for being an @$$!

You hug your mom, promise to stay safe, and head out the door.

You get into your sweet, super-new, super-classy luxury sedan that your daddy bought you, turning the AC up to full to thwart the oppressive summer heat. As you exit the gate, you wave at your guard Allah Ditta, feeling an odd tinge of regret (shotguns can be handy).

The streets are mostly silent - empty. Its an official holiday so people can go vote. Despite knowing this, the lack of traffic and humans is more than a little creepy.

Just ignore the T word (Taliban) and keep moving you think to yourself.

You reach Aaliya's house (mansion really - her family is super rich) and dial her on your mobile phone.

You: Hi, I'm downstairs. Lets head out!

Aaliya: Er...there is a slight problem.

You: What is it?

Aaliya: My dad says I can't go. Its too dangerous he says. He's a big shot bureaucrat as you know and...well...he says the threat of attack is very real...Can you come in and convince him its cool?

What do you say?

I'm coming in!

Er...I'll be on my way then

Why don't you sneak out?

> Page26
You say: Why don't you sneak out? - risky call there!

There is a long pause on the line...

Aaliya (slightly breathless): You...you think I could?

Score! She sounds like she'll do it!

You: Totally! Just lock your room door, exit from the window and make it to the gate."

Aaliya: Okay! I'm gonna do this! I'm sick of my dad controlling everything I do! I'll see you in a few. And...

You: What?

Aaliya: ...thank you.

You've scored some major points with Aaliya by tapping into her rebellious side! Good job! +5000 for you.

A few minutes later, Aaliya sneaks out her front gate and climbs into the car next to you. Shes crazy short, crazy petite and crazy cute. You've known her for a year now and have found her bubbly, effervescent personality a huge turn-on. Sadly, your class schedule at college has not given you two the opportunity to hang out much. As she grins at you, you feel your heart trying to thump its way out of your chest!

"Lets go, lets go! Quick before someone notices" says Aaliya.

You drive off with a screech. Aaliya squeals with glee - this is turning out great!

Head to the polling station

> Page30
You reach the polling station safely! Phew!

You pull up to your friendly neighbourhood polling station - a temporary setup inside an old, but cushy government office. You park your luxury sedan next to a line of other luxury vehicles (boy does it feel good to be rich!) and you and Aaliya stride towards the office, joining a small, orderly line of folk. Within minutes you are inside the polling station - this is proving to be really easy!

A few seconds later, you are face to face with your very first polling officer, a non-descript chap with a non-descript name tag and a non-descript uniform.

Random officer: Can I see your National ID Cards?

You: Sure officer, here you go!

(you hand him your NIC and Aaliya's.)

Random officer: Can't let you two in, sorry, move along...

WHAT?!?

You: There must be some mistake officer, we're both registered to vote! I checked mine with your SMS system just last week...

Random officer (deadpan voice): You're not on the list...

Your brain feel like it is about to explode.

What do you do?

Try to walk past the officer with an air of authority

Demand the officer recheck your names on the list

Tell Aaliya to use her feminine wiles

> Page51
You demand the officer recheck your names on the list - good for you!

The officer sighs and returns to his Pentium 1 computer. He spends several (achingly long) minutes staring at the screen and typing on the keyboard with one non-descript finger.

Finally he says...

"You're not on the list."

You are about to weep in frustration, Aaliya is questioning your manhood, and the small line behind you is now a lot longer and a lot angrier.

In a last ditch attempt you ask: Are you sure this computer is working properly? Maybe its not loading our names because the internet connection is down or something?

Random officer: We have no internet. This is only the voter list of those registered in this locale.

You: Er...can you check the full list online?

The officer thinks about this for a few minutes, then nods. He leaves his seat to go talk to his superiors (the ones who have internet) and returns - after 20 minutes...

Random officer: I've got good news, and bad news...which do you want first?

The bad news...

The good news!

> Page53
Bad news time...

Random officer: The bad news is...you both are registered to vote in  the Murdabad district of the city. Oh wait, that totally cancels out the good news about being able to vote but I guess...

You and Aaliya: AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA!

Murdabad (rough translation: where the dead live) is the roughest, toughest, meanest, ugliest, seediest, most-terror struck, AK47s-in-baby's hands, POOREST district in the entire city!

It seems your names were 'ghalti se' (rough translation: by mistake OR blatant rigging) moved to the Murdabad voter list at the last minute.

You turn and look Aaliya dead in the eye...she looks back at you, eyes widening, head shaking furiously back and forth.

"Babe...we're going to Murdabad and placing our #$%^ing votes..."

Aaliya slaps you for calling her babe, then you both exit the polling station and get in your car. You almost wish you had opted for Allah Ditta and his shotgun, but, well, a wannabe princess with daddy issues and political connections might come in handy? Maybe?

Head off to Murdabad

> Page54

On the way to Murdabad...

You have been driving for two hours now. The surrounding urban landscape has gone from trees and 1,200 yard houses to potholes, narrow roads, two-story high trash heaps and pollution so thick its making the car windows foggy.

You and Aaliya have been chit chatting for a while now, talking smack about your mutual peers. You are having such a good time, you barely notice being stuck in traffic next to heroin junkies shooting up with week-old needles on the roadside.

You do however notice the all-new stench of urine filtering through the car AC. You gag a little.  Aaliya shrieks and whips out perfume from her purse and douses the whole car with the stuff.

Now the car smells like vanilla, berries and urine. This whole voting adventure is starting to turn a bit too real for you - you are having second thoughts about going any further.

Even as you are considering this, Aaliya turns to you with a look of determination and says:

"Listen...I know what you're thinking, and trust me, I am freaking out a little myself...but we've come too far to turn back!"

"But...but...you do realize its going to get a whole lot smellier and dangerous right?" you say, "And...to be honest...I'm worried about what your dad will say about all this..."

Aaliya grins.

"Think about it this way," she says, "My dad will probably kill you either way for taking me into this neighbourhood, so whether we turn around now or later makes little difference!"

Now you're uber terrified.

What will you say to convince Aaliya turning around is a good idea?

Listen, I am in no mood to get killed either here, or by your dad

If we go back now, we'll be home in time to catch the new Game of Thrones episode

OMG is that a ZOMBIE eating a baby out there?!

> Page64
You say: Listen, I am in no mood to get killed either here, or by your dad - way to play it tough!

Aaliya is giving you that look. You've seen it before. She uses it in class anytime a boy tries to 'fraandship' her ardently. You feel the gaze piercing your skull and melting your brain just a little, but you keep up the tough guy approach and start scanning the road for the next u-turn.

Tsk tsk...you get -2000 for killing the mood and opting out of the adventure.

Aaliya is still glaring. Your brain melts a little more. You realize if this continues all the way home, you'll probably end up being a media studies grad from Iqra University. You turn to Aaliya and say...

"I'm sorry about what I said earlier. What I really meant by all that gibberish is that...well...I know voting is really important to both you and me...but...I put taking care of you well above the desire to vote..."

Your companion's face softens a little (you saved your brain!). She smiles. You smile back at her, mentally high-fiving yourself for convincing her that going back is a good idea AND slipping in the fact that you care for her. Odd, she's stopped smiling...

"LOOK OUT!" screams Aaliya.

You weren't pay attention to the road - there is a street urchin in your path, waving a pail and car-window wiper at you in horror as your car glides forward.

There is no chance your car will not hit the boy unless you act NOW!

What do you do?

Speed up, hit the kid, get out of here!

Take a hard left!

> Page62
You take a hard left!

Your quick action works, kind of.

Score +500 for taking a well-assessed risk!

The car's edge bumps into the kid, but barely grazes him. You on the other hand are careening down a narrow dirt path (calling it a road would be an injustice to roads the world over).

You almost kill several passersby, one stray dog and two irate chickens before finally coming to an abrupt halt. The dirt path is now too narrow to drive on. It continues to wind down, down, down and around, cutting a path through three story high makeshift homes (built illegal ala landgrabbing of course). This is a concrete and mud jungle that closes in so tight, you can barely see the grey, smoke-laden sky above.

A broken down, bullet-ridden paan-stained sign at the side of the path says:

WELCOME TO MURDABAD
(PLEASE KEEP YOUR GUN PERMIT ON YOU AT ALL TIMES)

Aaliya is super excited and can't wait to explore. She is already Instagramming a rat chowing down on a (you guessed it) rat bretheren. You on the other hand are not quite as enthused. Nothing you ever Googled on the democratic process included tips and tricks for your undertaking today.

You both get out of the car, locking it (hah!) and hoping for the best. Off you go down the path (of adventureee, whispers Aaliya). The good news is, the surrounding piles of filth and barricaded homes indicates you are definitely in Murdabad. The bad news is, the path you are on has a million other paths branching off of it.

Which direction would you like to go in?

Go right where the air seems less stale

Keep going straight

Go left where the muck seems less mucky

> Page77
You choose to go straight!

The rats seems to like this path in particular - you wonder if that is a good sign?

Ten minutes of walking later, Aaliya interrupts you and asks:

"Er...where are we going?"

"No idea, but if we keep walking, maybe we'll reach a major road or come across someone who can guide us," you reply.

"Well then I think we should head left," Aaliya says, "the stench of poop is a little less overwhelming down that way."

She's right about that.

What do you do?

Go right where you hear music playing

Keep going straight

Go left where the stench of poo is less overwhelming

> Page85
You go straight!

More rats. More muck. You feel well and truly lost in this maze now.

Luckily there is a grimy little stall with a grimy little man selling cigarettes and paan a little distance away. You walk up confidentally to the man and ask for the best path out of this place and on to the polling station.

The man leers at you two and says he'll tell you which way to go if you just give him your 'sweet smooth-skinned' companion's phone number. Aaliya goes pale (which does not help in this case) and you refuse.

"Fine," the man grunts, quite displeased.

"You want to reach the polling station? Just take the next left..."

What do you do?

Go right?!?

Listen to the man and go left?!?

Keep going straight

> Page87
You go straight - what's that saying about taking the straight path?

Booyaa!

The stench is far worse now, but the dilapidated homes around you give way to reveal a government-run building that is:

THE MURDABAD POLLING STATION!

You made it! Aaliya is jumping up and down for joy (catching pretty much every male eye in the vicinity)! You are doing your happy dance, and DAMN the muck that sticks to your designer shoes!

"We did it, we diddddd it," Aaliya sings. She skips over to you and gives you a warm hug!

"You're awesome," she whispers into your ear.

You gain +3000 points for winning Aaliya over, despite the odds!

A few minutes later you both get into line (holding hands) to caste your vote. You shuffle along for half and hour and are now face to face with yet another non-descript election official.

Random officer: Can I see your National ID Cards?

You: Sure officer, here you go!

(you hand him your NIC and Aaliya's)

Random officer: Can't let you two in, sorry, move along...

AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA!

Random officer: Oh wait, found your entries. You can go on in...

Phew!

You two separate, but not before Aaliya gives you a cheerful thumbs up. You are taken to a tiny room with a ballot box, a single ballot and an inkpad (to stick your thumb into and caste your vote).

You cover your thumb in ink. This is big, this is momunetal. You feel the future of Pakistan weighing heavy on your young shoulders. Your vote could very well be the deciding factor in this constituency! The options for the person you want to see in the National Assembly are in front of you.

Who do you vote for?

Pakistan Peoples Party (PPP) - Bilawal Bhutto Zardari

Pakistan Muslim League Nawaz (PML-N) - The 'One Pound Fish' guy

Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf (PTI) - Imran Khan

Muttahida Qaumi Movement (MQM) - Dr Farooq Sattar

Jamaat-e-Islami (JI) - Munawar Hasan

> Page113

You vote for PTI Chairman Imran Khan! CHANGE IS NIGH!

You are super psyched about your vote. You can't wait to get back to school and brag about voting for Immy K (the ladies are gonna loveee you!). Also, you want change, n' stuff...Oh yeah, and you want to be rid of all the old political elite because...well, because they're all evil and because Imran says so? You've never been political before but you figure you have done the right thing because the PTI definitely dominated Facebook and Twitter. Also change, n' stuff...

You try to victory dance to a Salman Ahmed song but end up only kinda swaying in an odd sufi manner before heading off to find Aaliya. Like you, she seems quite happy with her vote.

"Who did you vote for!" you ask Aaliya eagerly.

"I voted for IMRAN KHAN of course!" Aaliya says bouncing up and down (quite tantalizingly) with excitement, "Who did you vote for?"

What do you say?

I voted for Imran Khan too!

(Optional) Go back and vote differently

> Page119
You say you voted for Imran Khan too!

Without saying a word, Aaliya grabs your hand, drags you to the nearest empty room and kisses you on the lips!

You SCORE +20,000 for getting the girl!

You two make out for what seems like an eternity. In your head, you are sending out multiple blessings to democracy, to Imran bhai, to the choices you made leading you here...

Aaliya eventually pulls away, wiping her lipstick off your lips with a smile.

"Wanna exit this smelly hell-hole and hang out at my house?" She asks with a tone that promises this will be SO worth it.

"Lead the way babe," you say, as you pull Aaliya close for one last kiss.

You both head out, recover your car and drive off into the setting sun (and magical hearts appear in the sky).

GAME OVER

